    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Frans van Cranevelt to Miklós Oláh (Mechelen, 28 April
                    1537)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He wants to see Oláh’s <hi rend="italic">Hungaria</hi> in person as well,
                            but it has not happened yet. He is hawking his cento poems onto Oláh,
                            which Nanninck liked so much that he is pushing for their publication.
                            He is sending it to Oláh for review: if he likes it, it can be forwarded
                            to Nanninck, if he does not, he will destroy it. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nicolao Olao salutem plurimam. </p>
                <p>Cupio iampridem occasionem mihi dari istuc proficiscendi, ut <hi
                        rend="italic">Hungariam</hi> tuam videre liceat, sed hactenus fortuna nobis
                    id genus voluptatis invidit. Ego vero tibi meas nugas obtrudo, nisi potius
                    dicendum sit nec meas esse. Quippe <milestone unit="pb"/>qui alienis opibus abusus sum et Claudiani<note type="critic">Claudius
                        Claudianus (370–404), Roman poet.</note> labores in rem meam verterim,
                    centonem consarcinavi, sed non his legibus, quibus olim veteres et quibus
                        <persName>Ausonius</persName> in suo Virgilio centone<note type="critic"><hi
                            rend="italic">Cento nuptialis.</hi></note> sit usus. Ita tamen placuit
                    viro doctissimo ac communi amico domino <persName>Petro Nannio</persName>,<note
                        type="critic">Pieter Nanninck.</note> ut me vehementer urgeat ad edendum.
                    Mitto tibi opusculum ipsum cum illius epistolio, ut Dominatio Tua iudicet, quid
                    mihi faciendum sit. <del corresp="Olahus">Promitto</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">Permitto</add> tibi liberam statuendi facultatem, ut si edendum
                    videatur, recta via mittatur ad <persName>Nannium</persName>, sin minus, tum
                    quod ille dicebat <quote>de Apiace<note type="critic">I.e. Aiace.</note> caesar
                        noster: <del corresp="Olahus">concumbet</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                            type="corr">incumbet</add> in spongeam.</quote><note type="quote">Suet.
                            <hi rend="italic">De vitis caesarum,</hi> Div. Aug. 85: “respondit,
                        Aiacem suum in spongeam incubuisse”.</note> Vale, Vir Ornatissime et
                    Cranneveldium tuum, quod <del corresp="Olahus">facit</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">facis</add>, ama. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mechliniae</placeName> quarto Kalendas Maias anno 1537.</p>
            </div>
